</section>

{#- PAYOUT ANATOMY — content-to-goal table (cmp). -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="str-anatomy">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">How the books are built</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">What a short-term rental ledger does that a standard one can&rsquo;t.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">The difference between a generalist file and a short-term rental file isn&rsquo;t effort &mdash; it&rsquo;s the gap between a platform&rsquo;s net deposit and your real numbers. Each row below is a place vacation-rental accounting diverges from ordinary bookkeeping.</p>
    <table class="cmp">
      <caption class="sr-only">How short-term rental bookkeeping differs from standard company-wide bookkeeping</caption>
      <thead><tr><th scope="col">What it tracks</th><th scope="col" class="us">Short-term rental books</th><th scope="col">Standard books</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for r in anatomy %}
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" data-col="What it tracks">{{ r.cap | safe }}</th>
          <td class="us" data-col="Short-term rental books">{{ r.str | safe }}</td>
          <td data-col="Standard books">{{ r.std | safe }}</td>
        </tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p class="prose" style="margin-top:18px;">{{ anatomyNote | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

